children.text: This dwelling is in a designated termite zone, and the termite barriers have not been properly installed around the pipes/penetrations, with gaps in the collars greater than 0.4mm where termite access is possible, which can cause serious damage to the structure.
Part 3.1.4.3 Termite management systems of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that ‘Where a termite management system is required it must comply with AS 3660.1’.

The relevant Australian Standard AS 3660.1 Termite Management states in clause 5.3.6 Concrete slab penetrations, that ‘Attachment to the pipe or service shall be such that no gap is in excess of 0.4mm’.
These termite barriers will need properly installed prior to any concrete being poured in accordance with requirements of the BCA and AS 3660.
